-- PRESS DIGEST-Hong Kong - Jan 29
-- By Alice Woodhouse
-- Tue Jan 28, 2014 08:54PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, JAN 29 (Reuters) - These are some of the leading stories in Hong Kong newspapers on Wednesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST  -- Indonesia is in talks to send skilled workers such as construction workers and carers for the elderly to Hong Kong  even as the country plans to stop sending domestic workers overseas by 2017. (http://link.reuters.com/peq46v) -- Zimbabwe's government has filed a lawsuit over the ownership of a luxury home in Hong Kong which it claims was bought by a middleman in 2008 for HK$40 million ($5.2 million)as a home for Robert Mugabe's daughter while she studied in the city. (http://link.reuters.com/qeq46v) -- A suggestion by the Hong Kong Monetary Authority for banks to set aside as much as 3.5 percent of capital as a countercyclical buffer, higher than the 2.5 percent required by Basel, is being opposed from local lenders. (http://link.reuters.com/neq46v)  THE STANDARD -- The family at the head of Hong Kong's second largest developer Sun Hung Kai Properties <0016.HK> has resolved a feud over the entitlement to shares between three brothers, which have now been split equally. One of them, Walter Kwok Ping-sheung, has resigned as non-executive director of the firm. (http://link.reuters.com/weq46v)  HONG KONG ECONOMIC JOURNAL  -- Henderson Land Development <0012.HK> is to launch eight home projects in 2014 with a total 2,766 units and a sales target of HK$16 billion ($2.06 billion). For Chinese newspapers, see...............[PRESS/CN]